Before it became a trend, it was a statement.

In Episode 3 of Sartorial Stories, I explore the evolution of the pantsuit, how a piece of clothing stitched its way through decades of resistance, reinvention, and rebellion.

Strength training in your 30s isn’t just about building muscle, it’s about taking care of yourself in a way that really lasts. As women, our bodies naturally start to change around this time, metabolism slows down, muscle mass begins to dip, and bones need extra love to stay strong. That’s why lifting weights or doing resistance workouts matters so much. It helps keep your energy up, supports bone health, balances hormones, and even improves your posture. But beyond the physical, it’s a powerful confidence booster, making you feel stronger, more resilient, and ready to take on whatever life throws your way. 

So from one woman to another, if you’re thinking about starting, know that it’s never too late to give yourself this incredible gift. Your future self will thank you ✨

It’s the end of an era at Dior ! Maria Grazia Chiuri has just presented her final collection for the house. As Dior’s first female creative director, she brought a distinctly feminist lens to fashion, opening her tenure in 2016 for the now-iconic “We Should All Be Feminists” T-shirt. I remember being so awestruck by what she had created, I wore it endlessly because something about the moment & message stayed with me. Her first collection caused quite a stir, it shocked many, sparked widespread debate, and most importantly, it sold. She didn’t just make a statement; she started a dialogue and it had a profound impact on me.

Whether loved or critiqued (over the past few years, God knows there were moments I found myself completely baffled), her legacy at Dior is undeniable. She changed the tone and for a moment, fashion listened.
